cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about Named Entity Recognition (NER) which is a subfield of Natural Language Processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes an ontology-based approach which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The use of language information sources like Wiktionary suggests that the paper could also be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the focus on real-time applications and the use of fast methods suggests that the paper could also be categorized under cs.NE (Networking and Internet Architecture).
